  "text": "Round of 16 · 7 July 2026. Final score: USA 1–4 Belgium. Belgium ended the USA's home World Cup with a clinical, four-goal display.\n\nThe hosts dreamed of a deep run in front of their own fans; Belgium's golden-tinged generation had other ideas.\n\nThe goals, in sequence: 9′ Charles De Ketelaere — 0–1; 31′ Malik Tillman — 1–1; 33′ Charles De Ketelaere — 1–2; 57′ Hans Vanaken — 1–3; 93′ Romelu Lukaku — 1–4. That is 5 goals in all, USA accounting for 1 and Belgium 4.\n\nCharles De Ketelaere's first-half double did the early damage, either side of Malik Tillman's fine reply for the hosts. For a moment, at 2-1, the American crowd believed a comeback was on. Hans Vanaken's composed finish and a late Romelu Lukaku strike snuffed that out and made the scoreline emphatic. Belgium looked ruthless and experienced — the profile of a side that intends to be around in the final week.\n\nMomentum, as ever in the knockouts, proved a fragile and fleeting thing.\n\nThe expected-goals picture tightened around every set piece and transition.\n\nFine margins decided it, as they so often do at this stage of a tournament.\n\nFor the record, Belgium advanced. Goal, team and minute for every event above are Merkle-proven on Solana devnet via TxLINE; the scorer names are attributed from public match reports and aligned to the verified goals by team and order. Nothing here rests on the commentator's word alone.",
